---
import GlobalLayout from '../layouts/GlobalLayout.astro';
import Icon from '../components/ui/Icon.astro';
import { BEACONS_PROFILE } from '../utils/beacons';
---

<GlobalLayout
  title="About Giggi"
  description="Meet Giggi — cozy gaming creator from Argentina sharing dreamy games, desk setups, and a little corner of comfort on Mochileaf."
>
  <header class="animate-fade-in">
    <div class="page-container pt-10 pb-4 text-left lg:pt-12">
      <div class="flex items-start gap-4 sm:gap-5">
        <div
          class="flex h-14 w-14 shrink-0 items-center justify-center rounded-2xl bg-blossom-100 text-accent sm:h-16 sm:w-16"
          aria-hidden="true"
        >
          <Icon name="user-circle" size={36} weight="regular" />
        </div>
        <div class="min-w-0">
          <p class="mb-2 text-xs font-medium uppercase tracking-widest text-accent">About me</p>
          <h1 class="font-display text-3xl text-primary md:text-4xl">Hi lovelies! 🌸✨</h1>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </header>

  <div class="page-container-below-header space-y-14">
    <article class="prose-cozy max-w-3xl">
      <p>
        I’m Giggi, a cozy content creator from Argentina who’s completely in love with cozy gaming,
        Studio Ghibli vibes, pastel aesthetics, and cute little things that make everyday life feel
        magical 🧸🎐
      </p>
      <p>
        I created this space to share cozy games, dreamy desk setups, gaming inspiration, and a little
        corner of comfort for anyone who loves slow mornings, soft lights, relaxing worlds, and wholesome
        communities. Whether you’re here looking for your next cozy game obsession or just want to feel
        inspired while sipping your favorite drink, you’re always welcome here 💕
      </p>
      <p>
        When I’m not creating content, you’ll probably find me collecting manga, building cute keyboard
        setups, organizing my desk, watching anime, or spending time with my two pitbulls, Pipo and Nina
        🌷✨
      </p>
      <p>
        This website is my little cozy world on the internet, and I’m so happy you’re here 🍃
      </p>
    </article>

    <section aria-labelledby="mochileaf-story-heading">
      <h2 id="mochileaf-story-heading" class="section-title mb-6 flex items-center gap-2">
        <Icon name="plant" size={22} weight="regular" class="text-accent" aria-hidden="true" />
        How Mochileaf began
      </h2>
      <article class="prose-cozy max-w-3xl">
        <p>
          Mochileaf started as a small personal dream — a cozy little corner on the internet made for people
          who love relaxing games, comforting spaces, and creative inspiration 🌿✨
        </p>
        <p>
          At first, I simply wanted to build a place where cozy gamers could discover new games, setups,
          creators, and wholesome projects. But along the way, Mochileaf became something much more personal
          to me. It turned into a fun creative project where I could learn, experiment, and improve my web
          design and development skills while building something that truly feels like “me” 🧸💻
        </p>
        <p>
          One of my biggest goals with Mochileaf is to create a collaborative space where content creators and
          indie game developers can share little pieces of their projects, passions, and creativity with the
          community. I love the idea of supporting talented people, discovering hidden gems, and helping cozy
          projects feel seen and appreciated 🌸
        </p>
        <p>
          At the same time, I hope Mochileaf can continue growing into a real business and creative journey
          that allows me to keep evolving professionally, create new opportunities, and generate extra income
          to support my dreams. One of my biggest dreams is to visit Japan someday — a place that has inspired
          so much of the cozy and magical aesthetic behind everything I create 🍃✨
        </p>
        <p>
          More than anything, Mochileaf is a space built with love, creativity, curiosity, and the hope of
          making the internet feel a little softer and more inspiring for cozy gamers around the world 🤍
        </p>
      </article>
    </section>

    <section aria-labelledby="mochileaf-name-heading">
      <h2 id="mochileaf-name-heading" class="section-title mb-6 flex items-center gap-2">
        <Icon name="sparkle" size={22} weight="regular" class="text-accent" aria-hidden="true" />
        Why Mochileaf?
      </h2>
      <article class="prose-cozy max-w-3xl">
        <p>
          When I was choosing a name, I knew I wanted something cozy — a little generic and open enough to
          hold the worlds I love, but still tender and warm. Something that could wrap around games, setups,
          creators, and quiet inspiration without feeling boxed in.
        </p>
        <p>
          I played with a few ideas, and Mochileaf was the one that felt most like home: soft, peaceful, and
          comforting, like a place you’d want to settle into with a warm drink. It’s cozy on purpose — the
          kind of name that whispers “take your time” instead of shouting for attention 🍃
        </p>
      </article>
    </section>

    <article class="prose-cozy max-w-3xl">
      <p>
        I really hope you enjoy what I’m building here. Make yourself comfortable, wander at your own pace,
        and if any ideas, feedback, or cozy discoveries come to mind — I’d genuinely love to hear from you 💕
      </p>
    </article>

    <section
      class="panel-soft w-full p-8 text-center md:p-10"
      aria-labelledby="about-contact-heading"
    >
      <div
        class="mx-auto mb-4 flex h-12 w-12 items-center justify-center rounded-2xl bg-blossom-100 text-accent"
        aria-hidden="true"
      >
        <Icon name="chat-circle" size={26} weight="regular" />
      </div>
      <h2 id="about-contact-heading" class="font-display text-xl text-primary md:text-2xl">
        Share an idea with me
      </h2>
      <p class="mt-3 text-sm leading-relaxed text-secondary">
        Whether it’s a game we should cover, a creator to feature, a typo you spotted, or just a cozy hello —
        reach out anytime. I read every message when I can and I’m always happy to chat.
      </p>
      <a
        href={BEACONS_PROFILE}
        target="_blank"
        rel="noopener noreferrer"
        class="mt-6 inline-flex items-center justify-center gap-2 rounded-[var(--radius-pill)] border border-default bg-page px-6 py-3 text-sm font-semibold text-primary transition-all duration-300 hover:border-sage-300 hover:text-accent"
      >
        Contact via Beacons
        <Icon name="arrow-square-out" size={16} />
      </a>
    </section>
  </div>
</GlobalLayout>
